.TH "runic" "1" "" "" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
Runic \- Minimalist text editor written in pure Lua
.SH SYPNOSIS
\f[B]runic\f[R] [FILE]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]Runic\f[R] is a text editor designed to be simple and minimalistic.
The intent behind the creation of \f[B]Runic\f[R] was to make a modern
version of older editors such as Vim and Nano, while keeping the
efficieny that those editors bring.
.PP
\f[B]Runic\f[R] can be used with any plain text file.
Attempting to open a binary file or directory will crash the editor.
\f[B]Runic\f[R] is intented to be used for programming and general
editing of plain text files.
.SH BUILD SYSTEM
\f[B]Runic\f[R] uses a unique build system designed for portability.
Instead of using srlua and glue binaries (which are somewhat difficult
to install relative to other build systems), a Lua interpreter runs
\f[I]runic.lua\f[R] directly.
The actual \f[I]runic\f[R] command that is run is really just a shell
script.
This allows \f[B]Runic\f[R] to be installed on any platform that can run
Lua.
.PP
Alongside the \f[I]runic\f[R] binary, a \f[I]runic\-update\f[R] binary
is also provided.
More information about \f[I]runic\-update\f[R] can be found in
\f[B]runic\-update\f[R](1).
.SH DEPENDENCIES
